cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.NE

This paper presents a novel neural network architecture designed for explicit and expressive reasoning, which suggests it belongs to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The architecture is applied to the challenging CLEVR dataset for visual reasoning, indicating it may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper emphasizes the model's ability to learn iteratively and efficiently, suggesting it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper introduces a novel recurrent cell, indicating it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
